Cinder was looking out the viewport again, seeing earth approaching rapidly. 
Cyndro had taken over the navigations and was taking them on a safe and 
quick course to the battle involving the Maximals. They'd soon be there to 
help out, and Cinder's spark was pounding with anticipation. It wasn't often 
that she was allowed in battles, but it looked like Mantle was going to het 
her fight in this one. She really hoped that she would do good. This battle 
was special...

Cinder carefully turned her thoughts away from where they were heading. 
Extra excitement wouldn't be good for her right now, especially after so 
much time spent worrying about what happened to Striker's team. She just 
hoped that they were allright.

"Heavy thoughts?" Aqua's voice came from behind her, and she felt her 
brother's hand on her shoulder. Cinder nodded, not taking her eyes away from 
the viewport. Aqua was slightly annoying with his caring attitude sometimes, 
but this was one of the times when she was thankful for it, as she usually 
was.

"I guess. I hope we'll be there in time."

Aqua gave her a reassuring hug around the shoulders. "Don't worry. Cyndro 
will get us there.'

Cinder hugged Aqua back and then turned around and walked off toward the 
control room. Aqua followed her. Cinder stopped by her quarters, taking out 
a weapon that was a bit too big for her. She put it in a hip compartment and 
then walked out of her room, surprised to see Aqua still there. But she 
wasn't mad. She smiled and the two resumed their walk toward the control 
room.

The Element entered earth atmosphere, heading toward the Cybertronian Fire.
